127.5	Thomas_Pynchon	Thomas Pynchon	Thomas Ruggles Pynchon, Jr. (born May 8, 1937) is an American novelist. He is a MacArthur Fellow noted for his dense and complex novels, and both his fiction and non-fiction writings encompass a vast array of subject matter, styles and themes, including (but not limited to) the fields of history, science, and mathematics. For his most praised novel, Gravity's Rainbow, Pynchon won the 1974 U.S. National Book Award for Fiction and is regularly cited as a contender for the Nobel Prize in Literature.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/MutedPosthorn.png/220px-MutedPosthorn.png
